IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Connect Parent Group Network is an educational and research organization dedicated to supporting the implementation of the Connect Parent Group Programc. The Connect Parent Group Program supports parents foster parents and other caregivers to equip them with research-based parenting skills to effectively meet the needs of their children ages 8 to 18 especially those with behavioral challenges. The Connect Parent Group Network oversees and provides stewardship for ongoing implementation training and certification of providers to ensure adherence and fidelity to this evidence-based model. The Connect Parent Group Network also promotes peer-to-peer learning technical assistance and research between provider sites.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: In the first year of operation these policies and procedures were being developed and monitored by the Board of Directors during the meetings.

The compensation for the Executive Director and contractors was established in the grant award from the Annie E. Casey Foundation. The compensation was determined collaboratively after reviewing comparable compensation in other projects supported by the foundation and reviewed by the Board of Directors of the Connect Parent Group Network.

| Explanation:| The Connect Parent Group Network was formed in July 2021 to receive a grant from the Annie E. Casey Foundation to provide training and support in the implementation of an evidence-based parenting skills program the Connect Parent Group Program here in the U.S. The program originated in Canada. The fiscal year of the organization is the calendar year to fit to the grant reporting requirements. At the end of 2021 we should have filed this first 990. However we were confused about IRS requirements for entities only in operation for partial year. We are completing this now after having completed the required one for tax year 2022.
